OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,362,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1781637075
OL,3,CIsle of Man approves amendments to
OL,4,CAssisted Dying Bill
OL,6,FRoyal Assent for the bill was withheld
OL,7,Fby the government in April, it was the
OL,8,Ffirst time Royal Assent had been
OL,9,Fwithheld since 1972.
OL,11,FDr Alex Allinson, Member of the House
OL,12,Fof Keys and sponsor of the Assisted
OL,13,FDying Bill, said: "We are committed to
OL,14,Fworking with the Ministry of Justice
OL,15,Fto secure Royal Assent without further
OL,16,Fdelay, to give dying Manx citizens the
OL,17,Fend-of-life choice they want and
OL,18,Fdeserve.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,362,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1781637075
OL,3,CIsle of Man approves amendments to
OL,4,CAssisted Dying Bill
OL,6,F"The Isle of Man has properly
OL,7,Fdischarged democracy and shown that a
OL,8,Fcompassionate, well-designed law
OL,9,Fchange is achievable.
OL,11,F"I hope it gives confidence and
OL,12,Fencouragement to legislators at
OL,13,FWestminster that they can, and should,
OL,14,Fdo the same."
OL,16,FSarah Wootton, Chief Executive of
OL,17,FDignity in Dying, said: "Today is a
OL,18,Fprofound moment for the dying people
OL,19,Fof the Isle of Man who have fought so
OL,20,Fhard and waited so long for this law
OL,21,Fchange.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,362,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1781637075
OL,3,CIsle of Man approves amendments to
OL,4,CAssisted Dying Bill
OL,6,F"Thanks to Dr Alex Allinson's
OL,7,Fleadership and determination, and the
OL,8,Fbravery of individuals like Sue
OL,9,FBiggerstaff and Millie Blenkinsop-
OL,10,FFrench who shared their most personal
OL,11,Fstories to make the case for change,
OL,12,Fthe Isle of Man has made history.
OL,14,F"This is what good law-making looks
OL,15,Flike, careful, compassionate, and
OL,16,Fbuilt on listening to the people it
OL,17,Fwill affect most.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,362,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1781637075
OL,3,CIsle of Man approves amendments to
OL,4,CAssisted Dying Bill
OL,6,F"The Isle of Man and Jersey have
OL,7,Fdemonstrated that robust, well-
OL,8,Fdesigned assisted dying legislation is
OL,9,Fnot only possible, but commands
OL,10,Foverwhelming public and parliamentary
OL,11,Fsupport when legislators are given the
OL,12,Fchance to consider it properly."
OL,14,FThe milestone comes on the same week
OL,15,Fthat Labour MP Lauren Edwards
OL,16,Fannounced her intention to reintroduce
OL,17,Fthe Terminally Ill Adults (End of
OL,18,FLife) Bill at Westminster.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,362,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1781637075
OL,3,CIsle of Man approves amendments to
OL,4,CAssisted Dying Bill
OL,6,FThe original Bill, first brought by
OL,7,FKim Leadbeater MP, passed two votes in
OL,8,Fthe House of Commons with strong
OL,9,Fpublic and parliamentary support
OL,10,Fbefore a handful of anti-choice Peers
OL,11,Fblocked it from ever reaching a vote
OL,12,Fin the Lords.
OL,14,FSarah added: "The momentum behind this
OL,15,Fcause is now undeniable... Today
OL,16,Fshould give every MP the confidence to
OL,17,Ffinish what they started."
OL,19,FA Commons debate and vote on Lauren
OL,20,FEdwards' Bill is expected in September.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
